<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Essentially a locally evolved species related to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ampullacea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea ampullacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with pink flowers adapted for insect pollination.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
There is an unexpected record from Sonora (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T.R. Van Devender &amp; A.L. Reina-G</emphasis>
. 99-548 (MO), which we have not seen.
</paragraph>
